Package: fastBCR
Type: Package
Title: a k-mer-based approach for fast inferencing clonal families from large-scale B cell repertoire sequencing data
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Kaixuan Wang, Xihao Hu, Jian Zhang*
Maintainer: Kaixuan Wang <3018241020@tju.edu.cn>
Description: fastBCR is an automatic BCR clonal family inference method, which also incorporates multiple functional modules for downstream analyses. fastBCR is composed of three parts: Data Processing, BCR Clustering, and Downstream Analysis.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.2.0),
    ggplot2,
    statnet,
    msa,
Imports:
    dplyr,
    Biostrings,
    RColorBrewer,
    stringr,
    ggtree,
    ape,
    ggseqlogo,
    ggpubr,
    reshape2,
    GGally,
    magrittr
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
